snippet.textDisplay:
Hey Chris! Can you (or can you ask your doctor, if you're not feeling well enough?) report on pregnant mothers and what the risks are for them and their unborn babies!?!? Please??

I just met a mother, who is expecting her first grandchild. (It's her daughter who is pregnant.)

She's 34 weeks along, and she has been INCREDIBLY sick. It took 5 days to get results back. (She's in Alabama.) She tested positive for Corona virus yesterday. Her doc is doing an emergency c-section this morning.
No family can be in the room for the delivery of her 1st baby- because of the Virus.
The baby will be taken immediately from her and to his own room, and no family can be with him either- because of the Virus.
She won't get to hold him, or kiss him, no breastfeeding, nothing. Because of the virus.
They're warning her it may be 2 weeks or longer before she meets her baby boy. 😔 All because of this awful virus!!

I'm begging that someone speak on this, because we've heard so much about the elderly. Which I get. And people with underlying health issues. I get that too.

But I honestly hadn't thought of pregnant mama's!

(We've been staying home for weeks now, and we're in AZ.)

But because so much focus has been on the elderly, I'm certain there are others like me!
Who doesn't have anyone pregnant around them right now, so the expecting mama's of the world had slipped their minds!

Plus, I had recently been so irritated with the number of senior citizens I was (and still am) seeing at the grocery store, I didn't know how to feel about it! Each time I would go, I kept noticing older customers buying ONE thing! (Seriously, an elderly man was in front of me in line buying a box of granola bars, and another elderly man was behind me in the line buying a bag of chips. One bag of chips!)

Meanwhile, I have four kids age 14, 13, 10 and 8 years old that I am keeping inside as much as possible and have been for 3 weeks now.
But just this morning I witnessed a man and woman easily in their 70's, turning into the grocery store parking lot, driving a little convertible with the top down! 😤
Normally I would LOVE seeing that! I would hope that that would be me in the future! But now! Why??
We're being told to practice social distancing, and that "it's not just about us". So much focus has been put on the elderly (which is needed, I get it).

BUT.... after seeing this soon-to-be grandma cry tears through the shift we worked together- for fear that she might lose her firstborn daughter or her firstborn grandbaby or even both! Because of this virus... It just broke my heart. 😔
She needs a lot of prayer. (Her name is Aaliyah and she is in Alabama.) Starting with a prayer of Thanksgiving- that she is 34 or so weeks along! And can have the C-section! What about the mom who is only 22 weeks along?

There should be more emphasis on the importance of social distancing for them too...

Please forgive the length of this comment. And Chris, I pray that you too, retain the strength needed to beat this virus! You are a blessing to a lot of our world's. You and your doctor! We need you both here a lot longer! ❤

We're being told to practice social distancing,  and that "it's not just about us".  So much focus has been put on the elderly (which is needed, I get it). 

BUT.... after seeing this soon-to-be grandma cry tears through the shift we worked together- for fear that she might lose her firstborn daughter or her firstborn grandbaby or even both! Because of this virus... It just broke my heart. 😔 
She needs a lot of prayer. (Her name is Aaliyah and she is in Alabama.) Starting with a prayer of Thanksgiving- that she is 34 or so weeks along! And can have the C-section! What about the mom who is only 22 weeks along? 

There should be more emphasis on the importance of social distancing for them too... 

Please forgive the length of this comment. And Chris, I pray that you too, retain the strength needed to beat this virus! You are a blessing to a lot of our world's. You and your doctor! We need you both here a lot longer! ❤

Hey guys, Chris, Sanjay, and everyone else,
what about the Zinc?!
These several lab tests from the last 10 years about the use of Chloroquine and Zinc show that the virus replication inside the cells is reduced with the increase of Zinc (also INSIDE the cells!).
And they study the role of Chloroquine as a Zinc Ionophore. The trouble being that Zinc can't get inside cells on its own because it's an ion.
I know people have some amount of Zinc in their blood, but that can vary drastically and should be main metric in these tests (and probably of the blood picture of every patient given Chloroquine in a hospital, so soon we'll have more stats to analyze), but so far I haven't found anyone discussing Chloroquine to even mention Zinc! Why is that?
Do you have more detailed info?
Any info can be useful!

snippet.textDisplay:
Hey everyone, after watching a few videos of patients tested positive for COVID-19, keeping all the suffering and distress aside, I realized how truly lonely some of the people were. Considering the fact that very little is known about the virus and variance of the symptoms in general, it's just great to know that you are not alone in this fight.


This group is directed towards anyone who has been affected by the COVID-19 in some way. I wanted to build a kind of community so that people who test positive, know that they aren't alone, can speak to others who are in a similar situation and fight the virus with Hope, Conviction, and a strong frame of mind.


People who want to share positive messages, listen and encourage those who are in some way affected by the virus, are welcome to be a part of this community!


Let's build a family with resilience and a strong mindset to push through these hard times.


I request everyone to be a part of this process - share the link, especially with people who have been tested positive. This is truly a family of fighters in the making 😊

snippet.textOriginal:
Hey everyone, after watching a few videos of patients tested positive for COVID-19, keeping all the suffering and distress aside, I realized how truly lonely some of the people were. Considering the fact that very little is known about the virus and variance of the symptoms in general, it's just great to know that you are not alone in this fight.


This group is directed towards anyone who has been affected by the COVID-19 in some way. I wanted to build a kind of community so that people who test positive, know that they aren't alone, can speak to others who are in a similar situation and fight the virus with Hope, Conviction, and a strong frame of mind.


People who want to share positive messages, listen and encourage those who are in some way affected by the virus, are welcome to be a part of this community!


Let's build a family with resilience and a strong mindset to push through these hard times.


I request everyone to be a part of this process - share the link, especially with people who have been tested positive. This is truly a family of fighters in the making 😊
